we built a RAG system by converting structured policy data into natural language documents, chunking them, and generating embeddings using a local sentence-transformer model. These embeddings are indexed using FAISS for fast similarity search. For each user query, relevant policy chunks are retrieved and passed to an LLM to generate a grounded, cited response. All queries are logged with confidence scores and sources for auditability. Additionally, we implemented Genie for SQL-style business queries, enabling a complete policy assistant system.